annotation.TEXT: And now she's started tossing fireballs, and whoa! Okay, I guess she can abruptly change direction at any time now.

What the heck? I have no idea how I caught that kicked orb. Normally, if you're sliding and a kicked shell hits you in the back of the head, you kill the shell, right? (Actually, the orb wasn't in "kicked" mode anymore, since the blue duder had just "grabbed" it just before they both hit me while I was sliding, allowing me to grab it.)
Peaceful waterfall
BGM: TH06 - Septette for the Dead Queen

Whoa. Gotta ride this winged block here. I wonder what's in it... Well, I'm not going to sacrifice 20 energy to the pit to find out, but if I find something I can throw at it later on in this room, I'll come back.
Oh, geez. And now there are shurikens, which are being thrown in an arc. Welp, forget getting through this flawlessly.
BGM: TH06 - Stage 5 - The Maid and the Pocket Watch of Blood
Also, Sakuya's now added fireballs into the mix, which doesn't really mean much at this point, because I've already given up trying to dodge stuff.
Uh, oh. Blind jumps? Well, at least there isn't any ugly terrain where I'm landing. Just bullets that I can still see with no problem.
Alright, it's boss time, against Remilia herself! Once again, it starts off simple.
Yeah, I think I'm just going to hang out around the lower-left corner for the time being.
So, place your votes for one of these levels, and we'll find out where I go next time! (Hopefully, no other levels will be as long as The Scarlet Devil...)
Careful. I wouldn't want to lose this thing to a bullet.
Argh! Again with the finicky wall springboards! And this time, it cost me 20 energy to the pit, and a few point items that I'm not going to try going back for.
Interestingly, standing in the lower-left corner here puts me in the perfect spot to stomp one of the bullets.
Okay, fifth phase. Will this be the final pattern? Let's find out...
Looks like there's a couple Japanese characters made out of point items here. What do they say? (They say "Touhou", of course.)
There's another one of those dotted green blocks...
To be continued...
Okay, next phase. Also, I noticed she did a jump near the end of the previous phase. Will she be doing more jumping here?
Yep, she's begun pooping out more Eeries. And I bet that... yep, there's the shurikens.
Okay, third phase. She's just sitting there in the middle of those spell circles, shooting fireballs at me.
Looks like just a dead-end with a power up, which I'll certainly take.
Okay, here's where I was when I turned around before.
Nuts! I was thinking for a moment that I had to spin jump off of the Roto-Disc, but as you just saw, I can't do that, so how do you reach the highest point items?
Alrighty then. We've got these three levels left to pick from.
Whoa, just managed to dodge that Roto-Disc.
And now we've got more shurikens too.
And now back to our regularly scheduled farfignewton!
Uh, oh. The screen's getting darker. Please don't do the strobe light thing!

Huh, somewhere in the middle of all that, my energy changed by an unusual amount. (Looking back, I grabbed one of the power ups shortly after taking a hit, which caused that hit to only subtract 14 from my HP.)
Here's the third pattern. Wow, the game's being generous with the power ups, probably because it's practically impossible to avoid getting hit a lot.
Okay, I got a decent combo there... And that's it! The Scarlet Devil is completed at last! Wow, that was a long level!
Monster combo! (10 hits)
Whoa, in this fourth phase, she's like homing in on me herself. However, unlike the evil homing bullets, this is kind of a good thing, because it makes attacking her easier!
Bad Apple!
Well, I guess I've got a weapon now, not that it's gonna be any good at this point, since this series of power ups most certainly means that I'm nearing the boss...
D'oh. I hate how finicky wall springboards are. Fortunately, there wasn't anything nasty below there.
D'oh. At least there's that power up I left behind right there.
Alright, it's time for the final showdown! But first, I gotta get through one more stage.
BGM: TH06 - Lunar Clock ~ Luna Dial
Oh, man! Now she's pooping out Eeries!
BGM: TH06 - Stage 6 - The Young Descendant of Tepes
I guess Roto-Discs are going to be a thing here.
This would be such an obvious life-farming spot if this hack was using the usual lives system.
Okay, she's sped up a bit...
...A single point item. Yay. (I had a feeling that's what it would contain, since the other possibilities could've been game-breaking, but I had to know for sure.)
Ooh! Something throwable! Yes, I am indeed going all the way back just to check out what's in that winged block! (Please be a feather!)
Oh, she's floating now. But, does that change much? She's still near the ground after all.
Argh. That bullet nicked a tiny corner of my shoe. (Possibly the same tiny corner that got OMNOMNOM-ed earlier in Meiling's section.)
Okay, now let's see what's in that block...
Last time, on Touhou Mario... I defeated Hong Meiling!
Huh. That revealed another part of the path leading to the warp star, but it appeared in kind of an odd location. I guess it's not going to be a completely straight path when it's completed.
Nuts. I'm not getting another perfect here...
...And I also defeated Patchouli Knowledge!
Triple combo! (3 hits)
Sorry to waste everyone's time with that. Let me just get back to where I was...
Do any of these miscellaneous pipes actually lead anywhere? Or should I just stop checking them?
Whoa again! She started tossing shurikens! But, the next stomp after that ended the pattern before I took a hit, so I cleared that one perfectly!
Aw, I don't get to climb those stairs?
Maybe it'll be fairly quick, like in EoSD?
Huh, this battle wasn't preceeded by a bunch of power ups in a row like usual...
Alright, so now I've entered the third segment of The Scarlet Devil...
Nothing down there, I don't think. And with this power up up here, I'm back to maximum energy!
And now we're fence climbing, eh?
Nuts. Because of the sprite limit interfering with most of the bullet generators, I can't keep a continuous combo going. Oh, well. Just stomp her as fast as possible.
As usual, the fight starts off simple, but I bet she'll start tossing knives soon.
Hmm... If I go up, I won't be able to turn back, so let's check out the lower route first.
She's pooping out more Eeries, and tossing more shurikens, but that's doesn't really mean much now.
I might be able to reach a couple more with max speed jumps, but it's just not worth it. Fortunately, there's a power up here to replace the energy that I lost to the Roto-Disc.

Now, I've been told that there is a switch palace in the hack, but it's at the end of the game, after I've cleared everything else, which makes it kind of pointless. Still, I guess when the time comes, I can show it off a bit.
Okay, so Sakuya had four phases. (And Patchouli had three and Meiling had two. Looks like there's a pattern here, so I'm guessing Remilia will have five phases.)
Bah. It's obvious I'm going to get hit a lot here, so I'll just rapidly combo her.
Well, are you gonna fire? ...Guess not. For some reason, that spell circle's not doing anything. Whatever.
Total donations made so far: 2300 point items.
Anyway, I think I could use some healing, and Reimu could use some more donations.
Killer combo! (17 hits)
Whoops. Not what I intended to do.
Yay, I'm back at max energy again! At least this room's been generous with the power ups.
Yep, there are the knives, which are fired horizontally.
Oh, no. Another wall springboard! But, there's no way to mess this one up!
Triple combo! (3 hits)
Subterranean trip
Pfft... I forgot for a moment that that spell circle fired straight down.
D'oh. She hit me just after I got that power up, negating most of the gain (I only got 4 HP from it). Hmm... It seems like I'm more likely to dodge the stuff she shoots at me here as well.
There's a fourth pattern, too? But I get several power ups in this one. Just don't grab them too rapidly.
Alright, it's boss time! Oh, man! Look at Sakuya run!
